title: Simple meals for autistic adults | Pasta bolognese #actuallyautistic
description:
#autistic #adhd #aspergers #neurodivergent #neurodiverse 

What you'll need:

Pasta of choice 
2+ vegetables (fresh, tinned and/or frozen)
Protein of choice 
1 litre of water (or enough to cover the pasta)
Bolognese sauce
Salt and pepper to taste (optional)
Grated cheese (optional) 
Nutritional yeast flakes (optional) 

Method:

Bring the pot of water to the boil.
When it's reached boiling point, add the pasta and cook for the allocated time.
While the pasta is cooking, heat a pan for your protein source and veggies. 
Add a tablespoon of oil to the pan, allow it to heat for a minute and then add your protein and veggies. 
Fry the mixture for a few minutes/until cooked. 
Once cooked, add the pasta bolognese sauce to the pan and heat gently for 2 minutes. 
When the pasta is done, take it off the heat and drain it. 
Serve the pasta and the bolognese sauce.
Optionally, add your cheese and/or nutritional yeast flakes on top.

title: Simple meals for autistic adults | Hot dogs #actuallyautistic
description:
#autistic #adhd #aspergers #neurodivergent #neurodiverse 

Timestamps: 

0:00 Intro
0:11 Ingredients 
1:15 Hotdogs talk-through
3:45 Always refrigerate or freeze your leftovers! 
4:02 Outro

What you'll need:

Hotdogs
Hotdog buns
Onions
Gherkins
Tomatoes
Cheese (optional)
Optional sides (fries, chips, wedges, salad etc)
Condiments (ketchup, bbq sauce, mustard and/or other condiments)

*omit the condiments and/or other toppings if you don't like using them or they're too much for your senses. No shame in a naked hotdog.  

Method:

If you're making fries or chips as a side, put these in the oven and follow the cooking instructions on the packaging. 

Bring a pot of water to the boil. Once boiled, add your hotdogs to the water to cook for the time stated on your packaging. If your hotdogs have different cooking instructions, please follow them. 

If you're making a salad as a side, now would be the best time to chop your salad items and place them in a bowl. Add dressing if desired. 

When the hotdogs have finished cooking, remove them from the pot and place them onto a plate.

Assemble your hot dog buns with the hotdogs, onions, gherkins, tomatoes and/or any other food items you choose to use. 

Optionally, top with cheese and place your assembled hotdogs into the oven to grill for a minute or two/until the cheese has melted.

title: Simple meals for autistic adults | Ramen noodles #actuallyautistic
description:
#autistic #adhd #aspergers #neurodivergent #neurodiverse 

Timestamps: 

00:00 Intro
02:04 Ramen noodles
03:20 Cooking the veggies
04:29 Suggestions of other veg you can use with ramen noodles
06:42 How to save time when cooking
08:07 Suggestions of other food items you can pair with ramen noodles
10:04 Cooking the ramen noodles 
12:50 The logic behind washing up before you eat
12:19 Taste test 
13:32 Outro 

What you'll need:

Ramen noodles (with seasoning packet)
2 vegetables (fresh, tinned and/or frozen)
500ml water (use slightly more depending on your preference)

Method:

If using fresh vegetables that take a while to cook, boil them for a few minutes first and then add in the ramen noodles half way through cooking.

If using tinned vegetables, boil the ramen noodles first for a few minutes and then add the tinned vegetables in half way through cooking. 

If using frozen vegetables, add the frozen vegetables into the pot with the ramen noodles and boil everything at the same time. 

Choose whichever method you prefer. If the texture of food doesn't bother you, then no matter whether you use fresh, tinned or frozen, you can just add everything into the pot at the same time and boil it for 5 minutes or however long it says to boil the your ramen noodles for.

description:
Wanna support a small business and get your Hemp on? Find hemp bags and more at: https://hempnath.com

Some facts about Hemp material:

Hemp fabric is biodegradable, compostable and recyclable as well as  antibacterial, anti-fungal and anti-allergen. It is breathable and insulating due to the hollow shafts as well as being thermodynamic, which means that it keeps you warm when it‚Äôs cool and  keeps you cool when it‚Äôs hot.

Hemp is the worlds only naturally UV resistant fabric. It is an extremely durable, hard wearing fabric that only gets softer with age. It is a highly absorbent fabric which means that it retains it‚Äôs colour and quality when dyed, much more than cotton or linen alone.

Hemps strong structure means that it doesn‚Äôt lose it‚Äôs shape easily and it suffers less from creasing due to it‚Äôs elastic fibre. When Hemp is being grown, it cleans the soil around it, making it a great rotation crop.

Hemp needs less than 600L of water to produce 1kg of fibres which is much less than other materials which require upwards of 10,000L of water to produce 1kg of fibres.

title: Dear Autistic adults, why do you crave validation?
description:
Everyone needs support, encouragement and likes to be validated at some point and in some shape or form. However, when this need for outside validation is constant (and to the point where you feel like you won't be okay, unless you get this validation) I think there's a problem. There is no right way of doing anything (there are many different ways) and not one person has the answer to everything (some people may even unintentionally misguide you due to not knowing you well enough or understanding your unique challenges with Autism) so I think it's important to cultivate self-validation rather than relying on validation from other people, and also seek a professional and qualified therapist if needed (there are plenty of free services, if finances are an issue) to explore your feelings and/or behaviours in a safe space.

If you have any questions, submit them here: https://tellonym.me/IndigoChina

For US viewers,  purchasing Zyrtec is too expensive. Perrigo is a decent equivalent if you want to purchase online. But, overall, your best bet is to pick up any generic brand from the dollar store or walmart. 

If you'd rather purchase Piriteze or Perrigo online, I've included links below.

description:

The main aim of this series is to share my experience and express my emotions. I also want to be a voice for those who aren't able to or don't feel comfortable enough to express what they're going through. Sometimes, we can feel all alone in what we're experiencing when, in reality, that isn't the truth. Just hearing that someone else is going through the same or similar thing can be so comforting and reassuring. Thank you for tuning into this video, and I hope you found it useful and/or comforting. It's very important to remember that, no matter what you're going through, you are not alone.

title: Vive bars | Taste test | Review (discount in desc.)
description:
Vive bars are the perfect on-the-go snack for those of us who may be in a rush, but also want to eat clean and healthily. They're great for people with allergies to dairy, gluten and/or soya AND they contain zero refined sugars. Perfect if you're trying to lose weight (as they're low in calories) but also perfect if you're trying to gain weight (as they contain a decent amount of protein and are a clean source of additional calories) great all round!

The main ingredients are dates, peanuts, almonds, coconut nectar and pea protein. Very straightforward and simple which is what I like! Each 40 gram bar offers 10 grams of protein, around 5 grams fat, just over 15 grams carbohydrate, and a total of around 150 calories.

Thank you to EatVive for sending me these lovely bars in exchange for review. If you'd like to know more about EatVive and what they;re about, feel free to watch my first impressions video here: https://youtu.be/1Y23Rrdx9YA

title: Face Theory Skincare | First Impressions
description:
Face theory is a British skincare brand that offers a 3-step skincare routine. It is made up of cleansers, moisturisers, face oils and serums for all skin types. It was launched in April 2015 by Jamie Shuker.

The brand aims to 'change the skincare world' by offering a 'proven' beauty routine using only 'skin-friendly', 'paraben-free' ingredients.

In this video, I give you my first impressions of some of the products I purchased from Face Theory. 

Product list:

- Glycolic Exfoliating Cleanser/Face Scrub (E1)
- Clarifying Cleanser (C2) for Combination and Oily Skin
- 3 Tender touch Bamboo Face Cloths (100% Organic Bamboo) 
- Signature Moisturiser (M1) for combination skin

For product information, please visit the Face Theory website: https://www.facetheory.com

title: How to tell if a SHY guy likes you
description:
1. He'll stare at you from a distance, but as soon as you turn around, he'll look away as soon as possible.
2. He might act weird around you or seem very nervous.
3. He may not give you any eye contact at all.
4.  When he does look at you, his eyes may change slightly and get 'soft' or relaxed around the edges.
